</a> <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28691.To_Green_Angel_Tower__Memory__Sorrow__and_Thorn___3_' title='To Green Angel Tower (Memory, Sorrow, and Thorn, #3) by Tad Williams' rel='nofollow noopener'>To Green Angel Tower</a>, go I.<br/><br/></span>
  <span id="freeText17304761821852458873" style="display:none">Not quite as dramatic as the first book of this trilogy, but again, well written. Being a middle book, it ebbs and flows like an impatient stream itching to reach a river. Eventually, we get to the river, which is book three.<br><br>The author, in his acknowledgements calls <i>Memory, Sorrow, and Thorn</i> a bloated epic. A classic epic it is of good versus evil. Lots of characters, places and individual struggles to follow. So follow I will and onto book three, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28691.To_Green_Angel_Tower__Memory__Sorrow__and_Thorn___3_" title="To Green Angel Tower (Memory, Sorrow, and Thorn, #3) by Tad Williams" rel="nofollow noopener">
